Or where is there x,y, or z
type of social opportunity that

00:39:13.470 --> 00:39:17.330
I'm looking for,
dating opportunity,

00:39:17.330 --> 00:39:19.930
anything like that.

00:39:19.930 --> 00:39:25.180
Your tribe delivers to you
the most relevant, valuable,

00:39:25.180 --> 00:39:28.380
directed search
results possible.

00:39:28.380 --> 00:39:30.400
And it's a huge benefit,
both financially

00:39:30.400 --> 00:39:34.430
for economic opportunity, and
also for social opportunity.

00:39:34.430 --> 00:39:36.650
Who do you want to know?

00:39:36.650 --> 00:39:39.200
What kinds of events?

00:39:39.200 --> 00:39:42.980
These are the kind of things
that massively increase

00:39:42.980 --> 00:39:46.150
your felt sense of wealth.

00:39:46.150 --> 00:39:49.150
Because again, yes, money
in the bank is important.

00:39:49.150 --> 00:39:51.370
And we're, in no way,
here to deny that.

00:39:51.370 --> 00:39:53.880
But as important, if
not more important,

00:39:53.880 --> 00:39:58.090
is how you feel with the
opportunities and the things

00:39:58.090 --> 00:40:00.220
you're able to do
with that money.

00:40:00.220 --> 00:40:04.680
And your tribe
really is the filter

00:40:04.680 --> 00:40:08.690
through which the money
in your bank account

00:40:08.690 --> 00:40:11.310
is going to be filtered into
the experiences you have

00:40:11.310 --> 00:40:13.030
and whether those are
really, really rich

00:40:13.030 --> 00:40:15.730
and rewarding experiences
that feel incredibly

00:40:15.730 --> 00:40:18.430
meaningful to you over
time, or whether they're

00:40:18.430 --> 00:40:21.300
toss-away experiences
that you forget.

00:40:21.300 --> 00:40:24.830
BRYAN FRANKLIN: Tribe also has,
