00:44:32.640 --> 00:44:36.140
Because it's, again, different
perspectives on the same value.

00:44:36.140 --> 00:44:38.090
But diversity is essential.

00:44:38.090 --> 00:44:39.810
That's what I would say.

00:44:39.810 --> 00:44:41.260
MICHAEL ELLSBERG:
I would just add

00:44:41.260 --> 00:44:45.329
real quickly, if you think
of the word richness,

00:44:45.329 --> 00:44:46.370
it's a word I like a lot.

00:44:46.370 --> 00:44:49.820
Because it may seem
like rich means

00:44:49.820 --> 00:44:51.980
having lots of one thing,
like having lots of money

00:44:51.980 --> 00:44:53.700
or having lots of
gold, or whatever.

00:44:53.700 --> 00:44:55.074
But actually, if
you use the word

00:44:55.074 --> 00:44:57.840
rich as in the
richness of the novel's

00:44:57.840 --> 00:45:04.030
language or a rich flavor, or
a rich musical composition,

00:45:04.030 --> 00:45:07.870
what it actually means is lots
of different things interacting

00:45:07.870 --> 00:45:10.310
in very subtle and
interesting ways.

00:45:10.310 --> 00:45:15.740
And so yes, a tribe of
just rich white dudes

00:45:15.740 --> 00:45:19.240
might have a lot of financial
wealth running through it.

00:45:19.240 --> 00:45:21.740
And maybe that's what
those people want.

00:45:21.740 --> 00:45:23.991
But that's just
the financial side.

00:45:23.991 --> 00:45:26.365
Like Bryan said, I've hung
out with those kind of people.

00:45:26.365 --> 00:45:30.500
Anyone who's been to a party
of just one type of person

00:45:30.500 --> 00:45:33.410
in one economic class and
one race, or whatever,

00:45:33.410 --> 00:45:36.500
it doesn't have
that alive richness.

00:45:36.500 --> 00:45:41.000
To actually realize the
experiential side of wealth,

00:45:41.000 --> 00:45:44.500
you want a richness that is not
in the richness sense of lots

00:45:44.500 --> 00:45:48.550
of money, but a richness like
lots of different things,

00:45:48.550 --> 00:45:50.510
lots of different
kinds of people,

00:45:50.510 --> 00:45:54.590
different backgrounds,
different outlooks,

00:45:54.590 --> 00:45:58.140
interacting in ways, again,
with some shared value system.

00:45:58.140 --> 00:45:59.500
We don't want to cacophony

00:45:59.500 --> 00:46:01.070
But interacting
in different ways

00:46:01.070 --> 00:46:03.160
so that we're all
learning from each other.

00:46:03.160 --> 00:46:05.890
And that is much
more likely to lead

00:46:05.890 --> 00:46:09.089
to a richness of experience.

